<h1 class="hero-h">Fitagentic <em style="font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;font-style:italic;color:#00C853;">vs Zen Planner.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">An honest comparison for CrossFit boxes, martial arts academies, and small-group training studios. Zen Planner has been the category default for over a decade — and its billing engine is genuinely strong. Fitagentic is purpose-built for the AI agent work box operators wish their CRM did. Here's where each wins.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="disclosure" style="max-width:880px;margin:1rem auto;">
<strong>Disclosure:</strong> Treetop Growth Strategy is the marketing and thought-leadership arm of Fitagentic.ai's parent company. We have a commercial interest in Fitagentic. Zen Planner gets real wins below because it has earned them — that's the only way these comparisons are useful.
</div>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<span class="lbl">The TL;DR</span>
<h2 class="h2">The honest answer</h2>
<p class="body"><strong>Zen Planner is the stronger choice if</strong> you need bulletproof recurring billing, you sell retail through your box, you're running a programming-heavy operation (Daily WOD, belt progressions, skill tracks), or you're embedded in Zen Planner's ecosystem after years of operations.</p>
<p class="body"><strong>Fitagentic is the stronger choice if</strong> lead response speed, no-show recovery, retention, or labor cost is the bottleneck — or if you're a newer box where you'd rather build on an AI-native foundation than retrofit one onto a legacy CRM.</p>
<p class="body"><strong>The most common deployment for established boxes</strong> is Fitagentic alongside Zen Planner: Zen handles billing + programming + retail; Fitagentic handles lead conversations, no-show recovery, member retention agents.</p>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<span class="lbl">Where Zen Planner genuinely wins</span>
<h2 class="h2">The Zen Planner case</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Box-format DNA.</strong> Built specifically for CrossFit boxes and small-group training studios. Daily WOD scheduling, member skill tracking, belt and rank progressions for martial arts, drop-in management — all native.</li>
<li><strong>Recurring billing engine.</strong> One of the most mature billing systems in fitness software. Failed-payment retry logic, dunning, retail integration, tax handling — battle-tested across thousands of boxes.</li>
<li><strong>Retail integration.</strong> Selling supplements, apparel, equipment through the box is well-supported. Inventory, POS, member-charge-to-account — all integrated.</li>
<li><strong>Long-time category fit.</strong> 15+ years of focus on the box/academy format. Edge cases (drop-ins, hybrid memberships, family plans, military discounts) are handled.</li>
<li><strong>Strong community.</strong> Many box owners have used Zen Planner since opening; staff knows it well; the switching pain is real.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<span class="lbl">Where Fitagentic genuinely wins</span>
<h2 class="h2">The Fitagentic case</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>AI-native architecture.</strong> Conversational lead nurture, multi-turn rebooking, member retention agents. Zen Planner has marketing automation; Fitagentic has agents.</li>
<li><strong>Sub-60-second lead response.</strong> Most boxes running Zen Planner respond to inbound web leads within 2-8 hours via the coach or owner. Fitagentic responds in seconds with a contextual conversation. 60-second response correlates with 30-50% higher lead-to-tour conversion.</li>
<li><strong>No-show recovery as a default workflow.</strong> First-class drop-in no-show is a huge leak at most boxes. Fitagentic auto-rebooks 25-40% of no-shows.</li>
<li><strong>Member retention agents.</strong> Proactive outreach to members showing churn signals (drop in attendance, mid-cycle pause requests, declining engagement). Zen Planner has reporting; Fitagentic acts.</li>
<li><strong>Front-desk labor displacement.</strong> Many boxes run with the owner-coach doing front-desk work between classes. Fitagentic absorbs that work so the owner-coach can coach instead.</li>
<li><strong>Member-facing AI coaching.</strong> Movement scaling questions, "should I come in today" questions, recovery and mobility guidance.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<span class="lbl">Side-by-side</span>
<h2 class="h2">Honest feature comparison</h2>
<div class="table-wrap"><table class="t"><thead><tr><th>Dimension</th><th>Zen Planner</th><th>Fitagentic</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr><td>Box-format programming + WOD scheduling</td><td><strong>Stronger</strong> — purpose-built</td><td>Adequate via class management</td></tr>
<tr><td>Recurring billing engine</td><td><strong>Stronger</strong> — most mature in category</td><td>Solid; covers standard cases</td></tr>
<tr><td>Retail / POS integration</td><td><strong>Stronger</strong> — native</td><td>Limited; works via integration</td></tr>
<tr><td>Skill tracks + belt progressions</td><td><strong>Stronger</strong> for martial arts</td><td>Not a core focus</td></tr>
<tr><td>Lead response + conversion AI</td><td>Template marketing automation</td><td><strong>Stronger</strong> — conversational AI</td></tr>
<tr><td>No-show recovery</td><td>Manual</td><td><strong>Stronger</strong> — first-class workflow</td></tr>
<tr><td>Member retention agents</td><td>Reporting only</td><td><strong>Stronger</strong> — proactive outreach</td></tr>
<tr><td>Member-facing AI coaching</td><td>Not a focus</td><td><strong>Stronger</strong></td></tr>
<tr><td>Owner-coach time displacement</td><td>Modest</td><td><strong>Stronger</strong> — material time savings</td></tr>
<tr><td>Software-line monthly cost</td><td>$117-$307/loc</td><td>$250-$1,000/loc by volume</td></tr>
<tr><td>TCO including labor / owner time</td><td>Higher</td><td><strong>Stronger</strong> for most boxes</td></tr>
</tbody></table></div>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<span class="lbl">Common deployments</span>
<h2 class="h2">What box owners actually do</h2>
<h3 class="h3">Independent box under 150 members</h3>
<p class="body">Many replace Zen Planner outright if lead response and retention are the bottleneck and billing complexity is modest. Fitagentic handles lead nurture + retention; built-in billing covers standard cases.</p>
<h3 class="h3">Established box 150-400 members with retail</h3>
<p class="body">Most run Fitagentic alongside Zen Planner. Zen stays as system of record + retail engine; Fitagentic handles AI agent layer. Owner-coach gets time back to coach.</p>
<h3 class="h3">Multi-location box operator</h3>
<p class="body">Almost always Fitagentic alongside Zen Planner. The billing migration cost across multi-location accounts isn't worth the gain.</p>
</div></section>

